Class CompareFiles

  • java.lang.Object
    • classes.CompareFiles
  • public class CompareFiles

    • Constructor Detail

      • CompareFiles

        public CompareFiles​(java.lang.String csFileDefault,
                    java.lang.String csFileCreated)
        Constructor given two files.

        This is for the situation when User already has chosen to save an Excel file with his rules.

        Parameters:
        csFileDefault - Path of Excel file which contains code smells columns filled. We call this "Teorico" on the GUI.
        csFileCreated - Path of Excel file created when User already submitted metricsFile and saved rules, which will have code smells columns filled accordingly. We call this "Code Smells" on the GUI.

      • CompareFiles

        public CompareFiles​(java.lang.String csFileDefault,
                    java.lang.String metricsFile,
                    java.lang.String rulesFile)
        Constructor given three files.

        This is for the situation when User chose not to save an Excel file with his rules.

        Parameters:
        csFileDefault - Path of Excel file which contains code smells columns filled. We call this "Teorico" on the GUI.
        metricsFile - Path of Excel file after User submits project to be analyzed which won't have any code smells columns. We call this "Metricas" on the GUI.
        rulesFile - Path of text file after User submits and saves rules. We call this "Regras" on the GUI.

    • Method Detail

      • getColIndexesByTitles

        private java.util.LinkedHashMap<java.lang.String,​java.lang.Integer> getColIndexesByTitles()
                                                                                         throws java.lang.Exception
        Gets the corresponding Column Indexes of titles (code smells) that represent Column Titles in two Excel files.
        Returns:
        LinkedHashMap in which the String is the Column Title and the Integer is the corresponding Column Index per Excel file.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Propagated Exception from ExcelDealer to be dealt with on the GUI.

      • parseIndicator

        private static Indicator parseIndicator​(java.lang.String defaultText,
                                        java.lang.String createdText)
        Compares between two strings to return the right Indicator for each situation. Is used to compare String values of two Excel cells in method compareWith2Files and to compare String values of one Excel cell and one MethodRuleAnalysis map value in method compareWith3Files.
        Parameters:
        defaultText - Given string.
        createdText - Given string.
        Returns:
        Indicator This is the right Indicator after comparison of given strings.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - If given strings do not correspond to valid values.

      • compareWith2Files

        private Quality compareWith2Files()
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        When CompareFiles receives 2 Excel files ("Teorico" and "Code Smells"), this is the method that allows the comparison between them and the code smell detection quality evaluation.
        Returns:
        Quality object that contains both HashMaps with Indicators per Method and per Class.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Propagated Exception from ExcelDealer to be dealt with on the GUI.

      • compareWith3Files

        private Quality compareWith3Files()
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        When CompareFiles receives 3 files ("Teorico","Metricas" and "Regras"), this is the method that allows the comparison between them and the code smell detection quality evaluation.
        Returns:
        Quality object that contains both HashMaps with Indicators per Method and per Class.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Propagated Exception from ExcelDealer to be dealt with on the GUI.

      • matchesFields

        private boolean matchesFields​(MethodData dataDefaultExcel,
                              java.lang.String created_package,
                              java.lang.String created_class,
                              java.lang.String created_method)
        Overall, allows to know if package, class and method are the same between two files. This is an auxiliary method to avoid code repetition on CompareWith2Files and CompareWith3Files.
        Parameters:
        dataDefaultExcel - Given MethodData object obtained from DefaultExcel.
        created_package - Given String that should be the package name from CreatedExcel.
        created_class - Given String that should be the class name from CreatedExcel.
        created_method - Given String that should be the method name from CreatedExcel.
        Returns:
        Returns true if package, class and method are the same between two files.

      • testQuality

        public Quality testQuality()
                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Allows to evaluate the quality of code smell detection by choosing the right comparison method.
        Returns:
        Quality object that contains both HashMaps with Indicators per Method and per Class.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Propagated Exception from ExcelDealer to be dealt with on the GUI.
